In Week 18, the story is not of a single dramatic break but of many lines of pressure converging on the same point. Power thickens around the presidency, law bends more often toward weapon than limit, and the basic bargains of citizenship and care are rewritten in favor of the already strong. Yet the Democracy Clock does not move. It remains at 7:51 p.m., not because the week was safe, but because the damage it records is the deepening of patterns already present rather than a fresh breach. The week reads as a consolidation phase. What was signaled in earlier weeks is now being built into structure.\
